Thibaud Jean Leon Vallet and his cousin Jean Mickael Batrikian pleaded guilty to animal cruelty . 
  The pair lit a quokka on fire on Rottnest Island on April 3 . 
  They were ordered to pay $4000 and ordered to serve seven days in jail if they did not pay the fine . 
  The men were released from jail on Thursday after spending a week behind bars . 
  Animal rights activists have claimed the sentence was too lenient . 
  Footage emerged of the pair torching the creature with an aerosol can and a lighter . 
 